1
00:00:46,574 --> 00:00:48,494
So, answer me.

2
00:00:48,494 --> 00:00:51,484
Say you like me, too!

3
00:00:51,484 --> 00:00:53,574
President Gong Jin Dan!

4
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:09,090


5
00:01:11,944 --> 00:01:13,994
Did you hit me just now?

6
00:01:13,994 --> 00:01:16,374
What's with you, you bastard?

7
00:01:18,674 --> 00:01:21,014
What are you doing?

8
00:01:21,014 --> 00:01:22,964
Director! What are you doing?

9
00:01:22,964 --> 00:01:25,574
- How dare you flip out? 
 - Please stop!

10
00:01:25,574 --> 00:01:27,394
Let's go home!

11
00:01:28,854 --> 00:01:33,134
If you treat Ji Yeong like that one more time,

12
00:01:33,134 --> 00:01:35,354
I won't tolerate it anymore.

13
00:01:38,024 --> 00:01:40,354
Ji Yeong, let's go.

14
00:01:43,024 --> 00:01:45,314
   

15
00:01:49,104 --> 00:01:50,734
Are you okay, Ji Yeong?

16
00:01:50,734 --> 00:01:52,624
You were scared, weren't you?

17
00:01:53,244 --> 00:01:56,804
Yes, but I'm okay.

18
00:01:57,414 --> 00:01:59,084
But what happened?

19
00:01:59,084 --> 00:02:01,094
Why did he come here?

20
00:02:01,094 --> 00:02:04,574
The things his mother did to me by coming here...

21
00:02:04,574 --> 00:02:07,204
He said he came to apologize for that.

22
00:02:07,204 --> 00:02:10,964
I didn't want to hear it, and I didn't want to see him,

23
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:14,154
but I had to return the money she threw at me.

24
00:02:14,154 --> 00:02:17,414
There's no reason for me to take that.

25
00:02:17,414 --> 00:02:21,414
So, I went out to give it back to him.

26
00:02:21,414 --> 00:02:25,274
But he suddenly did that.

27
00:02:26,484 --> 00:02:28,704
Is he for real?

28
00:02:31,684 --> 00:02:35,824
Ji Yeong, I'm glad nothing happened to you.

29
00:02:36,824 --> 00:02:42,194
I know you were angry, but why did you have to punch him?

30
00:02:42,194 --> 00:02:46,754
Ji Yeong, I don't just punch people all the time.

31
00:02:46,754 --> 00:02:50,654
How could I have tolerated it when he was being violent to you?

32
00:02:50,654 --> 00:02:54,724
I won't hold back if he treats you like that again.

33
00:02:55,824 --> 00:02:57,744
Director...

34
00:02:58,954 --> 00:03:02,474
I think I'm touched right now.

35
00:03:03,614 --> 00:03:05,654
Don't be touched by stuff like this.

36
00:03:05,654 --> 00:03:08,824
You're my girlfriend. I need to protect you.

37
00:03:08,824 --> 00:03:11,214
Are you happy you're my girlfriend?

38
00:03:13,024 --> 00:03:15,164
Don't ever see that man again, okay?

39
00:03:15,164 --> 00:03:18,694
Of course, I won't. Why would I see someone like that?

40
00:03:18,694 --> 00:03:20,904
Do you think I went cuckoo?

41
00:03:21,904 --> 00:03:23,744
What did you say?

42
00:03:49,324 --> 00:03:51,234
Gong Jin Dan, youâ€”

43
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:55,054
Oh, my! What happened to your face? Who did that?

44
00:03:55,054 --> 00:03:57,284
Did you get beat up somewhere?

45
00:03:57,284 --> 00:04:00,284
Why would I get beat up? You think I let that happen?

46
00:04:00,284 --> 00:04:02,264
Why do you look like that if you weren't?

47
00:04:02,264 --> 00:04:03,714
Why is your lip bleeding? And why are you covered in dirt?

48
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:05,720
.

49
00:04:05,724 --> 00:04:08,214
What happened? Aren't you going to tell me?

50
00:04:08,214 --> 00:04:10,274
- This is all your fault! 
 - Gosh!

51
00:04:10,274 --> 00:04:11,874
- Get out of my room. 
 - Hey!

52
00:04:11,874 --> 00:04:15,044
- I don't want to talk to you! 
 - Gong Jin Dan!

53
00:04:16,434 --> 00:04:18,674
Shit!

54
00:04:24,184 --> 00:04:28,774
 And I already like someone. Don't ever come to see me again. 

55
00:04:32,064 --> 00:04:34,014
What's with Kim Ji Yeong?

56
00:04:34,644 --> 00:04:39,974
By chance... is she dating that Go Pil Sung?

57
00:04:40,764 --> 00:04:43,814
Seriously, are you kidding me?

58
00:04:49,864 --> 00:04:53,754
Ma Ri, here, it's a mango cake.

59
00:04:53,754 --> 00:04:56,564
Do Jun, it's me. Get the car ready.

60
00:04:58,164 --> 00:05:00,654
Where are you going?

61
00:05:00,654 --> 00:05:02,784
I'm going to Pil Sung Oppa's house.

62
00:05:02,784 --> 00:05:04,484
Ma Ri.

63
00:05:07,074 --> 00:05:08,784
Why would you go there?

64
00:05:08,784 --> 00:05:10,354
Why this time?

65
00:05:10,354 --> 00:05:12,534
To see Pil Sung Oppa.

66
00:05:13,094 --> 00:05:16,984
Ma Ri, why are you doing this?

67
00:05:16,984 --> 00:05:19,074
Mom, why are you so surprised?

68
00:05:19,074 --> 00:05:23,004
Are you worried I'd say something weird there?

69
00:05:23,004 --> 00:05:25,484
You're so shameless.

70
00:05:26,264 --> 00:05:27,394
What did you say?

71
00:05:27,394 --> 00:05:33,644
Mom, shouldn't you feel bad for Pil Sung Oppa and Seon Yeong?

72
00:05:33,644 --> 00:05:37,674
Are you only worried about me saying something there?

73
00:05:37,674 --> 00:05:39,534
Is that all you care about?

74
00:05:40,194 --> 00:05:41,314
Ma Ri.

75
00:05:41,314 --> 00:05:45,004
I can't just sit still like you.

76
00:05:45,004 --> 00:05:50,944
I feel so bad for Pil Sung and Seon Yeong that I can't just sit still like this!

77
00:05:50,944 --> 00:05:52,894
Hey, Ma Ri...

78
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,584
Ma Ri...

79
00:05:55,444 --> 00:05:58,954
This is a pearl necklace for Grandma.

80
00:05:58,954 --> 00:06:02,324
This is a purse for you, Ahjumma.

81
00:06:02,324 --> 00:06:05,184
This is a shirt for you, Ahjussi.

82
00:06:05,184 --> 00:06:09,094
- And these are sunglasses for Myeong Dong. 
 -  Wait...

83
00:06:09,094 --> 00:06:14,544
By the way, M-Ma Ri, what's all this?

84
00:06:19,174 --> 00:06:27,244
Thank you so much for raising Pil Sung Oppa as a great person.

85
00:06:30,734 --> 00:06:34,704
Ahjumma, you're such an angel.

86
00:06:34,704 --> 00:06:38,224
Thank you. I'm so thankful for you.

87
00:06:40,034 --> 00:06:44,194
 What kind of strategy is this now? 

88
00:06:47,184 --> 00:06:50,864
Ma Ri, why are you suddenly doing this?

89
00:06:50,864 --> 00:06:55,274
Why are you thanking us, and what are all these presents?

90
00:06:56,884 --> 00:07:01,044
I'm giving you these presents to apologize.

91
00:07:01,044 --> 00:07:05,764
I scared everyone by hiding in Pil Sung's closet last time.

92
00:07:05,764 --> 00:07:10,544
Things like that would never happen again.

93
00:07:10,544 --> 00:07:12,684
Because...

94
00:07:13,684 --> 00:07:19,594
I decided to think of Pil Sung as an older brother, not a man.

95
00:07:20,424 --> 00:07:25,634
Grandma, Ahjumma, Ahjussi, Myeong Dong,

96
00:07:25,634 --> 00:07:31,954
please think of me as Pil Sung's little sister from now on.

97
00:07:43,444 --> 00:07:45,564
 Look at this! This is... 

98
00:07:45,564 --> 00:07:48,124
The TV is too small.

99
00:07:48,124 --> 00:07:50,374
Should I get them a new TV, too?

100
00:07:56,214 --> 00:08:00,004
Will Ma Ri really only think of Pil Sung as an older brother?

101
00:08:00,004 --> 00:08:01,794
I'm telling you.

102
00:08:01,794 --> 00:08:05,224
She was confused because she was a lonely only child.

103
00:08:05,224 --> 00:08:08,144
She definitely doesn't think of him as her boyfriend.

104
00:08:08,144 --> 00:08:12,114
She said imagining kissing him makes her puke.

105
00:08:12,114 --> 00:08:16,394
Geez. He can't be her boyfriend, then. That'd be impossible.

106
00:08:16,394 --> 00:08:21,384
She said she'd visit us often as his little sister.

107
00:08:21,384 --> 00:08:25,794
She changes her mind all the time, I'm telling you.

108
00:08:25,794 --> 00:08:29,274
She really is strange.

109
00:08:29,274 --> 00:08:33,634
She's been playing us all this time.

110
00:08:33,634 --> 00:08:38,564
But I'm glad that she decided to be like this.

111
00:08:39,784 --> 00:08:42,704
 Ahjumma, when are we eating our noodles? 

112
00:08:42,704 --> 00:08:46,104
Wait just a moment, Ma Ri!

113
00:08:47,354 --> 00:08:49,394
It's all done.

114
00:08:50,274 --> 00:08:53,584
Ma Ri really said that?

115
00:08:53,584 --> 00:08:58,554
Yes. She said she's been lonely because she's an only child.

116
00:08:58,554 --> 00:09:01,594
 She thought of Pil Sung as an older brother. That's why she liked him. 

117
00:09:01,594 --> 00:09:04,394
 She mistakenly thought she wanted to date him. 

118
00:09:04,394 --> 00:09:08,634
 She doesn't want to marry him. She just wants him to be her older brother. 

119
00:09:10,614 --> 00:09:11,744
Really?

120
00:09:11,744 --> 00:09:14,614
 She apologized for going into his closet, too. 

121
00:09:14,614 --> 00:09:21,930
She even thanked me for raising Pil Sung as a great person.

122
00:09:22,794 --> 00:09:24,854
Oh, really?

123
00:09:24,854 --> 00:09:31,954
Anyway, Ma Ri brought us a designer purse, clothes, and

124
00:09:31,954 --> 00:09:34,984
all sorts of expensive things.

125
00:09:34,984 --> 00:09:39,074
I set them aside since I don't think it's right. I'll give them back next time we meet.

126
00:09:39,074 --> 00:09:42,374
Gosh, come on. No, it's okay.

127
00:09:42,374 --> 00:09:46,944
Just accept the presents since Ma Ri wanted you to have them.

128
00:09:46,944 --> 00:09:52,094
Looks like she brought them because she felt bad and grateful.

129
00:09:52,094 --> 00:09:56,714
That'd make her feel better, too. Please accept them.

130
00:09:58,864 --> 00:10:00,734
All right.

131
00:10:00,734 --> 00:10:03,434
Anyway, I called to let you know she's okay.

132
00:10:03,434 --> 00:10:05,824
She had noodles with us...

133
00:10:05,824 --> 00:10:09,334
and she's having fun with my mother-in-law.

134
00:10:09,334 --> 00:10:13,494
Yes, Seon Yeong. I'm sorry about everything.

135
00:10:13,494 --> 00:10:18,144
Ma Ri has been bothering you a lot, hasn't she?

136
00:10:18,144 --> 00:10:20,224
I'm so sorry for all the trouble.

137
00:10:20,224 --> 00:10:22,944
Gosh, what are you talking about?

138
00:10:22,944 --> 00:10:25,014
It's not like that at all.

139
00:10:25,014 --> 00:10:29,044
Don't worry. Ma Ri is basically my daughter.

140
00:10:29,044 --> 00:10:33,384
It's so nice to hear her chattering at our house.

141
00:10:33,384 --> 00:10:37,734
Our house used to feel like a temple, but it's filled with laughter now.

142
00:10:38,784 --> 00:10:43,184
Besides, Pil Sung is an only child, and so is Ma Ri.

143
00:10:43,184 --> 00:10:46,984
It'd be nice if they were like siblings.

144
00:10:46,984 --> 00:10:49,434
I'm so thankful that...

145
00:10:50,184 --> 00:10:53,884
you'd say that, Seon Yeong.

146
00:10:54,614 --> 00:10:55,884
Thank you so much.

147
00:10:55,884 --> 00:10:57,784
 Come on. Here we go again. 

148
00:10:57,784 --> 00:11:00,704
 Why do you always say that? 

149
00:11:00,704 --> 00:11:04,384
Anyway, she wants to see Pil Sung before she goes home. I'll send her home later.

150
00:11:04,384 --> 00:11:06,744
Okay. See you.

151
00:11:17,284 --> 00:11:19,194
Seon Yeong.

152
00:11:21,204 --> 00:11:24,754
Thank you so much, Seon Yeong. Thank you.

153
00:11:43,534 --> 00:11:45,174
What are you doing here this time?

154
00:11:45,174 --> 00:11:48,284
Hey, Kim Ji Yeong. Have you been two-timing?

155
00:11:48,284 --> 00:11:51,194
Pardon? What are you talking about?

156
00:11:51,194 --> 00:11:52,904
Don't you know what I'm talking about?

157
00:11:52,904 --> 00:11:54,804
You were seeing Go Pil Sung,

158
00:11:54,804 --> 00:11:58,104
but you said you'd think about it when I asked you to be my girlfriend.

159
00:11:58,104 --> 00:12:00,724
You've been testing and tempting me.

160
00:12:00,724 --> 00:12:02,794
But now you don't want me?

161
00:12:02,794 --> 00:12:06,844
You'd better compensate me for playing with my heart.

162
00:12:09,304 --> 00:12:16,494
President Gong, I never tempted or tested you.

163
00:12:16,494 --> 00:12:20,214
You told me to buy you meals instead of paying for the jacket.

164
00:12:20,214 --> 00:12:22,184
Since I didn't have money then,

165
00:12:22,184 --> 00:12:26,864
I was so grateful you told me to buy you meals instead.

166
00:12:26,864 --> 00:12:30,674
That's why I bought you meals. That's all.

167
00:12:31,724 --> 00:12:34,994
Hey, are you joking right now?

168
00:12:34,994 --> 00:12:37,714
You shouldn't have said you'd think about it, then.

169
00:12:37,714 --> 00:12:42,574
I already explained about that last time.

170
00:12:42,574 --> 00:12:44,724
I had to buy you another meal,

171
00:12:44,724 --> 00:12:48,574
but if I said no, it would've been difficult to eat together.

172
00:12:48,574 --> 00:12:51,064
That's why I said that.

173
00:12:51,624 --> 00:12:54,854
I said I'd think about it,

174
00:12:54,854 --> 00:12:57,664
but I didn't say I was interested in you.

175
00:12:57,664 --> 00:13:00,524
If I knew you'd be so mistaken,

176
00:13:00,524 --> 00:13:04,764
I would've paid you for the jacket even if I had to get a loan.

177
00:13:04,764 --> 00:13:08,554
I said all I needed to say. I need to get going.

178
00:13:08,554 --> 00:13:12,584
Hey, I'm not done talking. Where are you going?

179
00:13:13,104 --> 00:13:15,294
If you don't let go,

180
00:13:15,294 --> 00:13:21,424
I'll tell my boyfriend, the director, to beat you up again. Okay?

181
00:13:21,424 --> 00:13:22,914
What?

182
00:13:24,034 --> 00:13:28,114
Just be nice to your fiancee instead.

183
00:13:28,844 --> 00:13:30,744
You've got to be kidding.

184
00:13:30,744 --> 00:13:32,884
Don't ever come back here, okay?

185
00:13:32,884 --> 00:13:35,074
No one wants to see you.

186
00:13:38,124 --> 00:13:40,464
That country bumpkin!

187
00:13:40,464 --> 00:13:42,944
What do I do with her?

188
00:13:45,084 --> 00:13:46,284
You country bumpkin...

189
00:13:46,284 --> 00:13:48,574
Stop calling me that!

190
00:13:51,814 --> 00:13:53,584
   

191
00:13:54,294 --> 00:13:55,994
What?

192
00:13:57,744 --> 00:13:59,654
What did you say?

193
00:13:59,654 --> 00:14:01,404
Tae Hee?

194
00:14:02,324 --> 00:14:05,564
- I'm back. 
 - Hey, welcome back.

195
00:14:05,564 --> 00:14:07,284
Jin Dan, I'm here.

196
00:14:07,284 --> 00:14:10,044
Tae Hee, what's going on?

197
00:14:10,044 --> 00:14:13,794
Why didn't you call me? I would've picked you up, then.

198
00:14:13,794 --> 00:14:16,134
I wanted to surprise you.

199
00:14:16,134 --> 00:14:18,684
Actually, Mother invited me.

200
00:14:18,684 --> 00:14:20,534
Oh, really?

201
00:14:20,534 --> 00:14:23,884
Auntie and Chairman Gong were so curious about Tae Hee.

202
00:14:23,884 --> 00:14:28,264
You should visit Tae Hee's family, too.

203
00:14:28,264 --> 00:14:31,804
So, when would they like to have an in-laws' gathering?

204
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:36,404
They'd like to know if you're free for lunch next weekend.

205
00:14:36,404 --> 00:14:39,724
Chairman Gong, would you be free then?

206
00:14:39,724 --> 00:14:44,094
Of course. This is such a major family event.

207
00:14:44,094 --> 00:14:47,914
Soo Yeon, you should help us with it, too.

208
00:14:47,914 --> 00:14:49,944
Yes, Auntie.

209
00:14:51,214 --> 00:14:53,154
Try some of this.

210
00:15:05,884 --> 00:15:08,484
Did you drive Tae Hee home safely?

211
00:15:09,814 --> 00:15:11,304
Mom,

212
00:15:12,004 --> 00:15:15,694
why would you invite Tae Hee without telling me?

213
00:15:15,694 --> 00:15:17,984
And what's with the in-laws' gathering all of a sudden?

214
00:15:17,984 --> 00:15:22,304
It's not all of a sudden. It was brought up a long time ago.

215
00:15:22,304 --> 00:15:25,904
Why? Do you miss that girl or something?

216
00:15:25,904 --> 00:15:27,464
Is it because of her?

217
00:15:27,464 --> 00:15:30,384
Should I go berate her again? Should I?

218
00:15:30,384 --> 00:15:35,164
Mom, if you do that to Ji Yeong again, I might do something about it.

219
00:15:35,164 --> 00:15:37,494
Come to your senses, Gong Jin Dan!

220
00:15:39,634 --> 00:15:46,484
I've been hiding all of your crazy behaviors and waiting all this time.

221
00:15:47,234 --> 00:15:50,304
I thought you'd stop and come back at some point.

222
00:15:50,304 --> 00:15:51,924
But why are you acting like this?

223
00:15:51,924 --> 00:15:54,904
How far will you go? How far?

224
00:15:59,374 --> 00:16:04,364
Jin Dan, you can't do this to Tae Hee.

225
00:16:04,984 --> 00:16:09,514
You were with girls in the past you were crazy over and ended things on your own.

226
00:16:09,514 --> 00:16:12,064
But Tae Hee is different.

227
00:16:12,864 --> 00:16:15,984
Auntie, your brother, and sister-in-law.

228
00:16:15,984 --> 00:16:19,674
They're all happy and looking forward to you and Tae Hee's wedding.

229
00:16:19,674 --> 00:16:24,024
How could you get distracted by such a loser? How could you?

230
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:28,554
Do you really want to lose everything you have?

231
00:16:31,494 --> 00:16:33,434
No, Mom.

232
00:16:33,434 --> 00:16:35,964
I'm not that crazy.

233
00:16:37,754 --> 00:16:41,074
I won't do that again. Never again.

234
00:16:41,684 --> 00:16:43,684
Do you mean it?

235
00:16:43,684 --> 00:16:45,724
You mean it, right?

236
00:16:47,644 --> 00:16:53,954
 Yes, I can't abandon everything for a stupid woman like her. 

237
00:16:54,964 --> 00:16:57,944
Mom, I told you.

238
00:16:57,944 --> 00:17:00,104
I won't lose Tae Hee.

239
00:17:00,104 --> 00:17:03,044
I'll make sure to marry Tae Hee.

240
00:17:03,044 --> 00:17:05,774
Right, Jin Dan? Right?

241
00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:08,074
I'll count on you, okay?

242
00:17:16,514 --> 00:17:18,124
 I'm all done. 

243
00:17:18,124 --> 00:17:19,564
 Where are you, Ji Yeong? 

244
00:17:19,564 --> 00:17:21,904
 Are you finished with the reading? 

245
00:17:38,404 --> 00:17:40,024
I'm sorry, Director.

246
00:17:40,024 --> 00:17:42,344
I'm not done yet.

247
00:17:42,344 --> 00:17:46,964
Director Hong and the actors will read the script until late since the shooting starts next week.

248
00:17:46,964 --> 00:17:49,334
You should go home first.

249
00:17:50,144 --> 00:17:52,284
You want me to go home alone?

250
00:17:52,284 --> 00:17:55,884
I'd feel so bored driving alone.

251
00:17:56,484 --> 00:17:59,694
You're getting sillier and sillier.

252
00:17:59,694 --> 00:18:02,644
How did you live without me all this time?

253
00:18:02,644 --> 00:18:05,144
- Weren't you bored? 
 - This is no good.

254
00:18:05,144 --> 00:18:08,894
I should call Director Hong and ask him to finish it up now.

255
00:18:08,894 --> 00:18:10,644
So, we can have a date on the way home.

256
00:18:10,644 --> 00:18:14,354
Huh? No, no! You can't do that.

257
00:18:14,354 --> 00:18:17,984
I was kidding. I was kidding. Seriously, you're so easy to fool.

258
00:18:20,454 --> 00:18:22,944
You worked hard today, too.

259
00:18:22,944 --> 00:18:25,134
Go home early and rest.

260
00:18:25,134 --> 00:18:27,584
I'll text you when I'm done.

261
00:18:27,584 --> 00:18:29,414
Okay.

262
00:18:30,524 --> 00:18:34,234
Since we can't have a date,

263
00:18:34,974 --> 00:18:38,064
give me a hug instead. So I can go home.

264
00:18:43,154 --> 00:18:45,434
All right.

265
00:18:45,434 --> 00:18:49,804
Let's hug quickly before someone sees us.

266
00:18:58,334 --> 00:19:00,984
Do you want to borrow anything else?

267
00:19:00,984 --> 00:19:04,524
I'm sorry, Director! I'll get going!

268
00:19:06,824 --> 00:19:09,074
Director, what are you doing?

269
00:19:09,074 --> 00:19:10,514
Did you fall?

270
00:19:10,514 --> 00:19:13,694
Fall? No. My shoelace got undone.

271
00:19:20,224 --> 00:19:23,004
- We'll get going, then. 
 - Okay.

272
00:19:26,764 --> 00:19:29,104
Grandma, I love hearing Oppa's stories.

273
00:19:29,104 --> 00:19:30,784
Please tell me another one. Please.

274
00:19:30,784 --> 00:19:34,414
Should I tell you a story of him as a baby, then?

275
00:19:34,414 --> 00:19:36,814
As a baby? Yes, I love it.

276
00:19:36,814 --> 00:19:43,124
It was when he was about a year old when he was still crawling.

277
00:19:43,124 --> 00:19:48,614
He was by our side one moment, but he was gone a moment later.

278
00:19:48,614 --> 00:19:51,044
He was gone? Where?

279
00:19:51,044 --> 00:19:56,464
We didn't know then, either. So we searched the whole house, freaking out.

280
00:19:56,464 --> 00:20:00,154
My goodness. The baby who was crawling a moment ago

281
00:20:00,154 --> 00:20:04,094
somehow suddenly ended up on the rooftop.

282
00:20:04,094 --> 00:20:07,694
The rooftop? So? Did he get hurt?

283
00:20:07,694 --> 00:20:14,784
So the entire family was trembling nervously, hoping he didn't fall.

284
00:20:14,784 --> 00:20:20,654
But you know she's a mother.  She crawled gently toward him,

285
00:20:20,654 --> 00:20:24,494
grabbed him and brought him back.

286
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:29,144
Thank you. What a relief.

287
00:20:29,144 --> 00:20:32,534
Ahjumma, you're so admirable.

288
00:20:32,534 --> 00:20:33,794
What?

289
00:20:33,794 --> 00:20:37,644
And Grandma, Ahjussi, and Myeong Dong.

290
00:20:37,644 --> 00:20:42,714
You all raised Pil Sung Oppa as a healthy and strong person.

291
00:20:42,714 --> 00:20:44,684
You worked so hard.

292
00:20:44,684 --> 00:20:46,724
I'm so thankful for you.

293
00:20:46,724 --> 00:20:50,084
I'll never forget that you did that.

294
00:20:50,754 --> 00:20:54,364
Aigoo, aigoo. My gosh.

295
00:20:54,364 --> 00:20:57,674
- I'm home. 
 - Hey, Pil Sung.

296
00:20:58,914 --> 00:21:01,034
Ms. Ma Ri.

297
00:21:04,354 --> 00:21:06,004
Oppa.

298
00:21:07,314 --> 00:21:09,074
Yes, Ms. Ma Ri.

299
00:21:09,544 --> 00:21:14,814
From now on, call me "Ma Ri" instead of "Ms. Ma Ri."

300
00:21:14,814 --> 00:21:16,864
Because...

301
00:21:19,004 --> 00:21:22,274
I just want to be your little sister from now on.

302
00:21:22,274 --> 00:21:25,684
Just speak casually to me, too.

303
00:21:28,934 --> 00:21:30,614
Should I?

304
00:21:31,284 --> 00:21:33,104
Okay, Ma Ri.

305
00:21:33,104 --> 00:21:34,854
Okay.

306
00:21:34,854 --> 00:21:38,854
Oppa, I was raised all alone, and I was lonesome.

307
00:21:38,854 --> 00:21:41,584
So I've always wanted an older brother.

308
00:21:41,584 --> 00:21:45,384
What I really wanted was a real older brother figure like you.

309
00:21:46,094 --> 00:21:50,844
But I foolishly got confused and insisted you become my boyfriend.

310
00:21:51,414 --> 00:21:55,334
Oppa, I'm so sorry about everything.

311
00:21:55,334 --> 00:21:57,274
I apologize.

312
00:22:01,654 --> 00:22:03,224
I see.

313
00:22:03,224 --> 00:22:08,304
