318
00:22:22,444 --> 00:22:25,174
I'm happy to have a little sister, too.

319
00:22:25,174 --> 00:22:27,804
Really? Oppa, thank you so much.

320
00:22:27,804 --> 00:22:32,984
Let's shake hands to celebrate us becoming siblings, then.

321
00:22:38,036 --> 00:22:42,676
I heard you decided to be like siblings with Pil Sung.

322
00:22:42,676 --> 00:22:49,066
Yes. I was mad at you, hated you, and couldn't understand you.

323
00:22:49,066 --> 00:22:51,646
But Pil Sung Oppa said he'd be my older brother.

324
00:22:51,646 --> 00:22:53,946
So, I hate you a little less...

325
00:22:53,946 --> 00:22:58,166
and I'm thankful to you for giving birth to such a cool brother.

326
00:22:59,836 --> 00:23:01,486
Ma Ri,

327
00:23:02,486 --> 00:23:06,976
I'm so thankful that you're telling me that.

328
00:23:08,286 --> 00:23:12,706
Mom, I said I'm thankful you gave birth to him.

329
00:23:12,706 --> 00:23:14,616
But I still can't understand you.

330
00:23:14,616 --> 00:23:19,006
I never would've forgiven you if I were Pil Sung.

331
00:23:22,616 --> 00:23:24,526
Since we're on the topic,

332
00:23:24,526 --> 00:23:29,536
Mom, it's not too late to be nice to him if you feel bad.

333
00:23:30,496 --> 00:23:34,656
- What did you say? 
 - Mom, I want to share what I have with him.

334
00:23:34,656 --> 00:23:37,646
How can we make him as rich as we are?

335
00:23:37,646 --> 00:23:40,366
How can I share what I have with him?

336
00:23:40,366 --> 00:23:43,706
I can't tell Dad I want to give mine to Oppa.

337
00:23:43,706 --> 00:23:47,206
Because Dad can't know about him.

338
00:23:47,206 --> 00:23:51,036
How can we share what we have with him?

339
00:23:53,356 --> 00:23:55,696
Thank you so much, Ma Ri.

340
00:23:56,596 --> 00:24:00,316
You're a thousand times smarter

341
00:24:00,316 --> 00:24:03,076
and a better person than I am.

342
00:24:04,596 --> 00:24:06,436
You are.

