00:24:18,796 --> 00:24:21,456
It's not just a hit, but it's a smashing hit?

348
00:24:21,456 --> 00:24:25,556
I'm telling you. The first episode's ratings were over 15%.

349
00:24:25,556 --> 00:24:29,576
Ratings like this are considered a miracle.

350
00:24:29,576 --> 00:24:31,736
My goodness.

351
00:24:31,736 --> 00:24:34,586
We need to celebrate. Seriously.

352
00:24:34,586 --> 00:24:36,376
Aigoo, how amazing.

353
00:24:36,376 --> 00:24:41,346
Hold on. So, what would happen to Pil Sung going forward?

354
00:24:41,346 --> 00:24:44,386
Everyone would want to hire him now.

355
00:24:44,386 --> 00:24:48,216
Everyone will reach out to him once you create a hit show like this.

356
00:24:48,216 --> 00:24:49,876
Really?

357
00:24:49,876 --> 00:24:54,076
He just needs to choose whoever pays him more, then.

358
00:24:54,076 --> 00:24:58,496
No. He'd have to quit his job at the broadcasting station, then.

359
00:24:58,496 --> 00:25:02,366
Come on, Unni. There are so many freelancer directors these days.

360
00:25:02,366 --> 00:25:05,186
The world has completely changed now.

361
00:25:05,186 --> 00:25:08,066
I still prefer him to have a salary.

362
00:25:08,066 --> 00:25:11,656
He'd be guaranteed his job until he retires, too.

363
00:25:11,656 --> 00:25:16,686
Thinking about how worried I was when Hyeon Cheol said

364
00:25:16,686 --> 00:25:20,196
he'd quit his job and start a business,

365
00:25:20,196 --> 00:25:23,576
I don't want Pil Sung to go through that.

366
00:25:23,576 --> 00:25:27,976
I still wake up in the middle of the night thinking about it.

367
00:25:27,976 --> 00:25:33,676
Seon Yeong, do you have to bring up Hyeon Cheol's failure right now?

368
00:25:33,676 --> 00:25:36,416
Oh, Mother, it's not that.

369
00:25:36,416 --> 00:25:41,486
Anyway, don't encourage Pil Sung to do that, Myeong Dong.

370
00:25:41,486 --> 00:25:42,906
Okay.

371
00:25:42,906 --> 00:25:46,986
But you know he wouldn't listen to me even if I did.

372
00:25:46,986 --> 00:25:50,196
Hey, hey. So what if his show became a hit?

373
00:25:50,196 --> 00:25:51,856
He's dating the wrong person.

374
00:25:51,856 --> 00:25:54,456
Mom, why would you say that?

375
00:25:54,456 --> 00:25:57,026
What? I'm saying this for a reason.

376
00:25:57,026 --> 00:25:59,936
Not only is she a country bumpkin who has nothing,

377
00:25:59,936 --> 00:26:03,626
she's a gold digger who seduced an engaged man.

378
00:26:03,626 --> 00:26:09,466
Gosh! Anyway, why does Pil Sung have such poor taste in women?

379
00:26:10,356 --> 00:26:12,426
Don't worry, Mother.

380
00:26:12,426 --> 00:26:14,676
He'd give up eventually.

381
00:26:14,676 --> 00:26:18,796
Aigoo, aigoo. They're always together at home and at work.

382
00:26:18,796 --> 00:26:21,806
- Yeah, right! They'd break up. 
 - Mom!

383
00:26:21,806 --> 00:26:24,686
What? Did I say something wrong?

384
00:26:24,686 --> 00:26:26,776
That's enough.

385
00:26:28,376 --> 00:26:32,536
Director, have you considered my proposal?

386
00:26:32,536 --> 00:26:38,346
Yes, I appreciate you coming to see me and calling me several times.

387
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:43,416
But I'm not experienced enough to become a freelancer yet.

388
00:26:43,416 --> 00:26:45,606
I don't think it's the time yet.

389
00:26:46,436 --> 00:26:49,176
What is it? Are you not satisfied with the terms?

390
00:26:49,866 --> 00:26:52,386
It's not that.

391
00:26:52,386 --> 00:26:57,386
I don't think I'm ready to leave the broadcasting station yet.

392
00:26:57,386 --> 00:27:01,026
Let's talk when we get a chance later.

393
00:27:01,026 --> 00:27:03,676
Okay. I'll think about it...

394
00:27:03,676 --> 00:27:08,646
and come back with the terms you won't be able to refuse.

395
00:27:08,646 --> 00:27:11,376
You have to consider it then.

396
00:27:11,376 --> 00:27:13,006
Okay.

397
00:27:13,836 --> 00:27:15,536
Answer it. I'll be in touch.

398
00:27:15,536 --> 00:27:17,006
Okay.

399
00:27:17,676 --> 00:27:19,346
Thank you.

400
00:27:22,016 --> 00:27:23,616
Yes, Hyung.

401
00:27:24,846 --> 00:27:26,526
The station director?

402
00:27:27,696 --> 00:27:33,806
Pil Sung, the best production companies in the country

403
00:27:33,806 --> 00:27:37,876
are eager to recruit you, apparently.

404
00:27:37,876 --> 00:27:41,056
You're getting tons of calls already, aren't you?

405
00:27:41,056 --> 00:27:43,056
Not that much.

406
00:27:43,056 --> 00:27:47,086
You didn't meet any of the CEOs, then?

407
00:27:47,936 --> 00:27:50,626
Well, I did.

408
00:27:50,626 --> 00:27:57,596
Pil Sung, it's fair to say that I made you successful.

409
00:27:57,596 --> 00:28:01,126
You leaving the broadcasting station now is...

410
00:28:01,126 --> 00:28:05,076
to exaggerate it a bit, it's a betrayal.

411
00:28:05,076 --> 00:28:10,176
What I'm saying is that you should stay grounded.

412
00:28:10,176 --> 00:28:14,186
It's not like you and I had a dating relationship or something. What do you mean by "betrayal"?

413
00:28:14,186 --> 00:28:21,496
Pil Sung, the world looks rosy to you since you're here.

414
00:28:21,496 --> 00:28:23,096
This is a greenhouse.

415
00:28:23,096 --> 00:28:26,846
The outside is the Himalayas. Everything is covered with ice.

416
00:28:26,846 --> 00:28:31,636
Station Director, why are you scaring me when I'm just getting started?

417
00:28:31,636 --> 00:28:35,336
I'm not scaring you. I'm just worried about you.

418
00:28:35,336 --> 00:28:37,836
I'm telling you to think carefully.

419
00:28:37,836 --> 00:28:41,016
Okay. I'll think about it carefully.

420
00:28:41,016 --> 00:28:46,236
Yes. Think carefully... and stay here.

421
00:28:46,236 --> 00:28:48,026
What did you say?

422
00:28:48,026 --> 00:28:50,946
You want to start a drama production company?

423
00:28:51,946 --> 00:28:54,856
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

424
00:28:54,856 --> 00:28:58,126
It's not sudden. I've been talking about this for years.

425
00:28:58,126 --> 00:29:03,016
You told me to think about it after building experience running a store.

426
00:29:03,016 --> 00:29:06,516
I did say that.

427
00:29:06,516 --> 00:29:10,296
Do you not trust me? You look nervous.

428
00:29:10,296 --> 00:29:13,916
Of course I do. It's just so sudden.

429
00:29:13,916 --> 00:29:17,326
Dad, stop arguing and let her do what she wants.

430
00:29:17,326 --> 00:29:20,186
A man should be a man of your word.

431
00:29:22,086 --> 00:29:25,206
Yes, a promise is a promise. I should keep it.

432
00:29:25,206 --> 00:29:27,366
Since you run the store well, you'd be good at running a production company, too.

433
00:29:27,366 --> 00:29:30,716
you'd be good at running a production company, too.

