00:34:31,486 --> 00:34:33,276
Ji Yeong.

509
00:34:35,286 --> 00:34:37,376
Director.

510
00:34:38,296 --> 00:34:39,956
What's wrong, Ji Yeong?

511
00:34:39,956 --> 00:34:42,186
Did something happen on set?

512
00:34:42,186 --> 00:34:44,746
I'm the problem.

513
00:34:44,746 --> 00:34:50,256
I made a lot of mistakes today and I don't think I did as well as I wanted to.

514
00:34:51,606 --> 00:34:53,846
Is that why you're so down?

515
00:34:53,846 --> 00:34:55,706
Yes.

516
00:34:55,706 --> 00:34:57,506
Everyone's like that in the beginning.

517
00:34:57,506 --> 00:34:59,516
You mess up a lot since you're nervous.

518
00:34:59,516 --> 00:35:03,146
Some actors forget all the lines because of stage fright.

519
00:35:03,146 --> 00:35:06,666
One actor had one line, but he messed up over 30 times.

520
00:35:06,666 --> 00:35:09,686
We had to cancel the shoot because of him that day.

521
00:35:09,686 --> 00:35:13,616
That sounds made up.  You made that up, right?

522
00:35:13,616 --> 00:35:19,526
Well... I exaggerated it a tiny bit, but everyone's like that in the beginning.

523
00:35:20,426 --> 00:35:22,226
Thank you.

524
00:35:22,226 --> 00:35:28,626
I think I feel a little better since you said that.

525
00:35:28,626 --> 00:35:32,476
By the way, when will you stop calling me "Director"?

526
00:35:32,476 --> 00:35:35,426
Are we working right now? Aren't we dating?

527
00:35:35,426 --> 00:35:37,966
You still always call me "Director."

528
00:35:37,966 --> 00:35:40,426
What should I call you, then?

529
00:35:40,966 --> 00:35:44,606
Well, "Oppa" would be nice.

530
00:35:44,606 --> 00:35:46,746
What?

531
00:35:47,436 --> 00:35:50,136
I can't say stuff like that.

532
00:35:50,136 --> 00:35:54,596
And we're not siblings. What do you mean, "Oppa"?

533
00:35:54,596 --> 00:35:58,076
I hate calling my boyfriend "Oppa."

534
00:35:58,076 --> 00:36:00,826
Will you keep calling me "Director," then?

535
00:36:00,826 --> 00:36:03,566
No, but...

536
00:36:04,186 --> 00:36:06,476
How about "Pil Sung"?

537
00:36:06,476 --> 00:36:10,086
That's not bad, either.

538
00:36:11,846 --> 00:36:15,456
I'm not too thrilled about it, either.

539
00:36:15,456 --> 00:36:18,446
I'll give it a thought, then.

540
00:36:18,446 --> 00:36:20,836
What should I call you, then?

541
00:36:22,336 --> 00:36:23,746
Darling?

542
00:36:23,746 --> 00:36:25,106
Huh?

543
00:36:25,106 --> 00:36:27,456
- Baby? 
 - What?

544
00:36:27,456 --> 00:36:29,376
- Honey? 
 - Gosh!

545
00:36:29,376 --> 00:36:32,056
That's enough! Just call me by my name.

546
00:36:32,056 --> 00:36:34,286
The chills are killing me right now.

547
00:36:34,286 --> 00:36:37,326
Okay. You can't die from having the chills.

548
00:36:37,326 --> 00:36:39,916
I'll start with "Ji Yeong," then.

549
00:36:39,916 --> 00:36:45,836
Sounds good. I love it whenever you call my name.

550
00:36:45,836 --> 00:36:49,736
Okay. I prepared something to celebrate your first shoot.

551
00:36:49,736 --> 00:36:51,346
Let's get going.

552
00:36:51,346 --> 00:36:54,986
- What is it? 
 - You'll see when you get there.

553
00:36:54,986 --> 00:36:59,196
I'm curious. Can't you just tell me?

554
00:37:01,586 --> 00:37:05,266
Director, these are so pretty.

555
00:37:06,576 --> 00:37:10,006
There's a treasure box in there. Look for it.

556
00:37:10,006 --> 00:37:11,606
Okay.

557
00:37:17,936 --> 00:37:20,426
I-I found it.

558
00:37:20,426 --> 00:37:23,296
- Open it. 
 - Oh, okay.

559
00:37:32,946 --> 00:37:35,076
 I hope you always walk on the petal-filled path. 

560
00:37:35,076 --> 00:37:39,256
 Actor Kim Ji Yeong's forever No. 1 fan, Go Pil Sung. 

561
00:37:41,696 --> 00:37:43,756
Director.

562
00:37:45,096 --> 00:37:49,746
Whenever you feel stressed and sad, look at these and feel better.

563
00:37:49,746 --> 00:37:53,796
And let your anger out on this when you get mad at me.

564
00:37:53,796 --> 00:37:56,666
Can I, really?

565
00:37:56,666 --> 00:37:58,886
Will you actually do it?

566
00:38:01,146 --> 00:38:04,036
Why would I ever be mad at you?

567
00:38:04,036 --> 00:38:06,756
I'd never do it, Director.

568
00:38:06,756 --> 00:38:08,336
You're calling me "Director" again.

569
00:38:08,336 --> 00:38:10,966
Okay, fine, Pil Sung.

570
00:38:13,916 --> 00:38:15,576
What did you say?

571
00:38:16,376 --> 00:38:18,616
Yes, go ahead and call me that.

572
00:38:48,946 --> 00:38:51,656
It's my grandma. What do I do?

573
00:38:51,656 --> 00:38:55,016
Leave now, Director. It'd be bad if she finds out.

574
00:38:55,016 --> 00:38:57,636
She'd beat me to death!

575
00:38:57,636 --> 00:38:59,816
- What did I do? 
 - Leave, leave.

576
00:38:59,816 --> 00:39:03,136
- I'll go, then. 
 - Yes, bye!

577
00:39:09,256 --> 00:39:12,696
Aigoo, what's going on, Grandma?

578
00:39:12,696 --> 00:39:16,096
Why did you have to call me now?

579
00:39:16,096 --> 00:39:20,216
 I called because I wanted to hear your voice. 

580
00:39:20,216 --> 00:39:24,256
 Why are you yelling at me? 

581
00:39:24,256 --> 00:39:27,566
When did I yell at you?

582
00:39:27,566 --> 00:39:32,346
 Ji Yeong, you can't just date random people in Seoul. 

583
00:39:32,346 --> 00:39:35,706
 You can't just let anyone in at your place. 

584
00:39:35,706 --> 00:39:37,946
 Keep that in mind, okay? 

585
00:39:37,946 --> 00:39:40,976
Okay, I-I will.

586
00:39:40,976 --> 00:39:43,426
Why are you so worried?

587
00:39:43,426 --> 00:39:47,806
I-I'll talk to you later, then. Okay.

588
00:39:54,346 --> 00:39:58,176
How does Grandma know what's going on from there?

589
00:39:58,836 --> 00:40:02,676
I can't do anything because of her.

590
00:40:07,266 --> 00:40:11,876
By the way, what was that situation just now?

591
00:40:13,576 --> 00:40:18,856
Kim Ji Yeong, what are you imagining right now?

592
00:40:38,441 --> 00:40:42,721
Pil Sung, I started a production company.

593
00:40:43,661 --> 00:40:45,551
Production company?

594
00:40:46,751 --> 00:40:49,431
It's something I've been dreaming of for years.

595
00:40:49,431 --> 00:40:52,411
I'm thinking of finally doing it now.

596
00:40:52,411 --> 00:40:54,471
Oh, I see.

597
00:40:54,471 --> 00:40:59,711
So, I've been meeting directors and writers to sign contracts before the foundation ceremony.

598
00:41:00,471 --> 00:41:04,611
Would you like to help me, Pil Sung?

599
00:41:05,481 --> 00:41:06,851
Pardon?

600
00:41:06,851 --> 00:41:13,041
I want to sign Go Go Entertainment's first contract with you, Director Go Pil Sung.

601
00:41:13,041 --> 00:41:15,771
That's why I wanted to see you.

602
00:41:17,011 --> 00:41:18,301
With me?

603
00:41:18,301 --> 00:41:24,631
Yes. I really enjoyed your drama, "Don't Lie to Me."

604
00:41:24,631 --> 00:41:28,811
Your directing skills made it shine even more.

605
00:41:28,811 --> 00:41:32,251
That's why the whole world is focusing on you now.

606
00:41:32,861 --> 00:41:37,151
Pil Sung, please join my company.

607
00:41:42,391 --> 00:41:49,061
Ahjumma, I appreciate the offer, but I still need to build more experience.

608
00:41:49,061 --> 00:41:52,611
No, Director Go. You're good enough.

609
00:41:56,181 --> 00:41:57,641
This is the contract.

610
00:41:57,641 --> 00:42:01,131
Do you want to look through it now?

611
00:42:01,131 --> 00:42:04,101
And let me know if it's missing something.

612
00:42:18,251 --> 00:42:19,811
This is...

613
00:42:20,391 --> 00:42:22,981
The contract fee is too high.

614
00:42:22,981 --> 00:42:27,831
What are you talking about? I'm doing this since you're worth it.

615
00:42:27,831 --> 00:42:32,851
I heard other production companies are desperate to hire you, too.

616
00:42:32,851 --> 00:42:36,731
Shouldn't I offer at least this much to have the edge?

617
00:42:37,691 --> 00:42:39,301
Ahjumma.

618
00:42:40,041 --> 00:42:46,761
I want Go Go Entertainment to be Korea's best drama production company.

619
00:42:46,761 --> 00:42:49,121
As long as you join me,

620
00:42:49,121 --> 00:42:54,631
I'll fully support you so you can tell the stories you want to tell.

621
00:42:55,391 --> 00:42:58,981
I'm just getting started. So I need a trustworthy person.

622
00:42:58,981 --> 00:43:05,621
Director Go. I mean, Pil Sung... please help me.

623
00:43:11,691 --> 00:43:15,061
Okay, I'll think about it.

624
00:43:29,031 --> 00:43:35,021
 I want Go Go Entertainment to be the best drama production company in Korea. 

625
00:43:35,021 --> 00:43:37,621
 As long as you join me, 

626
00:43:37,621 --> 00:43:43,341
 I'll fully support you so you can tell the stories you want to tell. 

627
00:43:45,951 --> 00:43:48,711
 I'll make two billion if I do this for a few hours. 

628
00:43:48,711 --> 00:43:50,661
 Can you give me that money? 

629
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:52,421
 I'll be the one who'd regret it. 

630
00:43:52,421 --> 00:43:55,511
 So, shut up and leave unless you have two billion! 

631
00:43:55,511 --> 00:43:57,331
 Two billion? 

632
00:43:59,231 --> 00:44:01,411
 No, I don't. 

633
00:44:03,001 --> 00:44:07,891
 Not two billion, 200 million, 

634
00:44:08,791 --> 00:44:11,341
 or even 20 million won. 

635
00:44:13,761 --> 00:44:17,391
 But I can give you two billion won. 

636
00:44:18,911 --> 00:44:21,441
 If I save on everything else... 

637
00:44:22,171 --> 00:44:25,031
 and make things work, 

638
00:44:26,341 --> 00:44:29,721
 I can give you around two million. 

639
00:44:35,861 --> 00:44:38,611
I'll never stumble again.

640
00:44:39,881 --> 00:44:46,641
I won't lose the one I love because of a lack of power and money again.

641
00:44:47,771 --> 00:44:49,431
Never again.

642
00:44:55,741 --> 00:44:57,251
What did you say?

643
00:44:57,251 --> 00:45:00,951
You'll join the company Soo Yeon is starting?

644
00:45:00,951 --> 00:45:02,541
Yes.

645
00:45:04,141 --> 00:45:09,261
Do you mean you'll quit your job at the broadcasting station?

646
00:45:09,921 --> 00:45:11,591
Yes.

647
00:45:11,591 --> 00:45:16,431
Soo Yeon's company made me an amazing offer.

648
00:45:16,431 --> 00:45:20,751
I don't think I'll get a chance like that again, so I want to give it a try.

649
00:45:22,121 --> 00:45:27,891
But Pil Sung, can you think about it more carefully?

650
00:45:27,891 --> 00:45:34,181
The moment you leave your job, you'll lose the shield that's been protecting you.

651
00:45:34,181 --> 00:45:39,641
If you stay at the station you're guaranteed your retirement, and you'd be stable.

652
00:45:39,641 --> 00:45:46,011
Even if you failed a few times, you'd be given new chances.

653
00:45:46,011 --> 00:45:53,091
But once you fail as a freelance director, it'd be so hard to get another chance.

654
00:45:53,091 --> 00:45:55,961
Yes, think about it one more time.

655
00:45:55,961 --> 00:45:59,231
Isn't it better to be stable?

656
00:46:00,691 --> 00:46:06,051
It'd be hard once I quit my job, but I want to be successful on my own.

657
00:46:06,051 --> 00:46:08,251
I want to make money that way, too.

658
00:46:08,931 --> 00:46:11,811
I want to have faith in myself and go for it.

659
00:46:11,811 --> 00:46:14,081
So, don't worry so much.

660
00:46:14,941 --> 00:46:17,911
Okay. Fine.

661
00:46:17,911 --> 00:46:21,051
You should do that if you've decided to do that.

662
00:46:21,051 --> 00:46:25,551
Okay. Do a great job since you've decided to do it.

663
00:46:25,551 --> 00:46:27,471
Be sure to be successful.

664
00:46:28,371 --> 00:46:32,011
Yes, they'd pay him much more than other places.

665
00:46:32,011 --> 00:46:33,941
Why say no?

666
00:46:33,941 --> 00:46:36,061
Pil Sung, you're doing the right thing.

667
00:46:36,061 --> 00:46:39,761
You're supposed to row when the water's flooding in.

668
00:46:39,761 --> 00:46:44,171
It won't fail since it's a production company under the APP Group.

669
00:46:44,171 --> 00:46:46,941
Anyway, that's great news. Congratulations.

670
00:46:53,331 --> 00:46:55,711
Yes, I understand.

671
00:46:55,711 --> 00:46:58,271
I have faith in you, too, son.

672
00:46:59,571 --> 00:47:03,911
Thank you, Mom, Dad, Grandma, and Aunt.

673
00:47:05,131 --> 00:47:06,921
What did you say?

674
00:47:06,921 --> 00:47:11,231
You're paying that much contract fee to Director Go?

675
00:47:11,231 --> 00:47:15,281
Why would you pay that much money to a newbie director?

676
00:47:16,201 --> 00:47:18,781
Are you out of your mind, Soo Yeon?

677
00:47:18,781 --> 00:47:23,081
Jin Dan, how dare you talk to your sister-in-law like that?

678
00:47:23,081 --> 00:47:25,021
"Out of your mind?"

679
00:47:25,021 --> 00:47:26,851
I'm sorry.

680
00:47:26,851 --> 00:47:30,221
But this is totally unprecedented.

681
00:47:30,221 --> 00:47:35,761
If you pay a newbie director that much, you'd have to raise the pay of other directors, too.

682
00:47:35,761 --> 00:47:38,151
You'd get criticized by other companies.

683
00:47:38,151 --> 00:47:41,761
This goes against the business ethics.

684
00:47:41,761 --> 00:47:46,871
Soo Yeon, is it because he's your friend's son, by chance?

685
00:47:47,841 --> 00:47:52,051
That's not why. How could you ask that?

686
00:47:52,051 --> 00:47:54,611
Director Go isn't a newbie director.

687
00:47:54,611 --> 00:47:57,521
He's one of the hottest directors right now.

688
00:47:57,521 --> 00:48:00,011
Of course, he doesn't have a lot of experience,

689
00:48:00,011 --> 00:48:04,171
but he won an award at an international festival with a mini-series two years ago.

690
00:48:04,171 --> 00:48:08,741
He was nominated for the Juniper Award for a drama named "Don't Lie to Me."

691
00:48:08,741 --> 00:48:11,431
He's receiving attention internationally, too.

692
00:48:11,431 --> 00:48:14,191
That's why other production companies want him.

693
00:48:14,191 --> 00:48:16,811
But I managed to persuade him.

694
00:48:16,811 --> 00:48:18,991
But I'm still against it.

695
00:48:20,421 --> 00:48:24,371
I'm the CEO of Go Go Entertainment. Why are you telling me this?

696
00:48:24,371 --> 00:48:29,001
Soo Yeon, Angel Investment invested in your company, too.

697
00:48:29,001 --> 00:48:31,281
Because Hyung told me to.

698
00:48:31,281 --> 00:48:34,311
So, I have the right to speak up.

699
00:48:35,381 --> 00:48:38,521
Anyway, Director Go is no good. I'm against it.

700
00:48:38,521 --> 00:48:41,281
So, meet other directors instead.

701
00:48:41,281 --> 00:48:44,351
How dare you tell Mom what to do, Uncle?

702
00:48:45,981 --> 00:48:48,821
How much did you invest that you're butting in?

703
00:48:48,821 --> 00:48:52,641
How much did you invest? Dad, sell my stocks and pay him that money.

704
00:48:52,641 --> 00:48:53,751
Oh, my.

705
00:48:53,751 --> 00:48:58,101
Gong Ma Ri. How dare you talk to Uncle like that?

706
00:48:58,101 --> 00:49:02,301
Uncle, don't meddle with my mom's business and focus on your job.

707
00:49:02,301 --> 00:49:04,811
Should I name all of your failed businesses?

708
00:49:04,811 --> 00:49:07,681
The condos in Vietnam, Myanmar, and Lemon Construction.

709
00:49:07,681 --> 00:49:11,341
- You thought I didn't know, right? 
 - My gosh, Ma Ri.

710
00:49:11,341 --> 00:49:16,921
Ma Ri, your mom has no experience, but she's trying to run a production company.

711
00:49:16,921 --> 00:49:20,051
Uncle was saying that out of concern.

712
00:49:20,601 --> 00:49:22,581
Don't worry, Great Aunt.

713
00:49:22,581 --> 00:49:25,811
Pil Sung will become a huge director.

714
00:49:25,811 --> 00:49:28,941
My mom will never fail.

715
00:49:34,291 --> 00:49:36,701
   

716
00:49:39,071 --> 00:49:42,751
Here. You can sign here.

717
00:49:42,751 --> 00:49:44,321
Okay.

718
00:49:54,161 --> 00:49:57,371
Director Go, I look forward to working with you.

719
00:49:57,371 --> 00:50:00,341
Yes, likewise.

720
00:50:00,341 --> 00:50:02,221
Let's make this work.

721
00:50:02,221 --> 00:50:05,111
Yes. I'll do my best.

722
00:50:13,841 --> 00:50:15,701
What's this?

723
00:50:15,701 --> 00:50:19,031
Looks like a bankbook. Is there money in it?

724
00:50:19,031 --> 00:50:22,051
Gosh, did you already receive the contract fee?

725
00:50:22,051 --> 00:50:23,711
Yes.

726
00:50:24,511 --> 00:50:27,701
Pil Sung, why would you give this to me?

727
00:50:27,701 --> 00:50:30,511
It's your money. You should manage it.

728
00:50:30,511 --> 00:50:35,201
Mom, pay off the loan with this first.

729
00:50:35,201 --> 00:50:37,241
And Dad, you wanted to start a business.

730
00:50:37,241 --> 00:50:39,441
Do whatever you want to do with it.

731
00:50:40,061 --> 00:50:44,271
Gosh, n-no! We can't accept this money.

732
00:50:44,271 --> 00:50:49,351
You've been working hard to pay off the loan all this time.

733
00:50:49,351 --> 00:50:55,011
Keep this with you and use it when you move out or get married.

734
00:50:55,011 --> 00:50:59,021
Seon Yeong, he wants to do his duty as a son.

735
00:50:59,021 --> 00:51:01,681
Why stop him?

736
00:51:01,681 --> 00:51:04,251
Pil Sung, thank you.

737
00:51:04,251 --> 00:51:06,951
You're surely a good son.

738
00:51:06,951 --> 00:51:10,131
You're willing to give this much to your father.

739
00:51:10,131 --> 00:51:14,171
Pil Sung, it was worth raising you all this time.

740
00:51:14,171 --> 00:51:16,531
Gosh, no, Mother.

741
00:51:16,531 --> 00:51:20,371
Pil Sung, this isn't free money.

742
00:51:20,371 --> 00:51:23,091
You need to prove your worth with your work.

743
00:51:23,091 --> 00:51:25,211
So, you should manage it.

744
00:51:25,211 --> 00:51:30,051
Mom, I'm not giving you all of it. I set some aside already.

745
00:51:30,051 --> 00:51:31,991
So don't worry.

746
00:51:31,991 --> 00:51:34,721
And I'll make even more money going forward.

747
00:51:34,721 --> 00:51:36,921
So, it's okay.

748
00:51:36,921 --> 00:51:41,581
And you've gone through a lot raising me all this time.

749
00:51:41,581 --> 00:51:43,901
This is the least I can do.

750
00:51:48,381 --> 00:51:50,401
Pil Sung.

751
00:51:50,401 --> 00:51:52,741
Gosh, seriously.

752
00:51:52,741 --> 00:51:56,031
Yes. Yes, Pil Sung.

753
00:51:56,031 --> 00:51:57,951
Thank you so much.

754
00:51:57,951 --> 00:52:01,481
You did a great thing. Thank you, Pil Sung.

755
00:52:04,551 --> 00:52:06,441
My goodness...

756
00:52:44,651 --> 00:52:47,471
Aren't you Myeong Dong's boyfriend?

757
00:52:48,221 --> 00:52:50,961
I'm sorry. I thought you were someone else.

758
00:52:50,961 --> 00:52:52,731
I'm sorry.

